The two fundamental properties of each network are their spatial composition and time-dependent behavior, which depend on the cortical regions they include and the sequences of states appearing in their time-series, respectively. We hence started with a control procedure to evaluate the dependence of μ[Φmax] and the reference metrics on these properties. To test spatial dependency, we generated a series of control networks by randomly grouping five regions from different RSNs and computing μ[Φmax] for each random collection of regions. To evaluate temporal dependence, we maintained each network’s regions but permuted the sequences of states appearing in their time-series (i.e., the order of time-points was shuffled). In Fig. 2, we present the results of these permutations for each metric in comparison to the original networks.Fig. 2Results from spatial and temporal control procedures.
