The table was used to compute a χ2 value, which indicates the extent to which the time-series deviates from the Markov property.71 This can be seen as a comparison between the sequence distribution of the time-series to that of a sequence distribution that satisfies the Markov property (i.e., the goodness of fit of a Markovian distribution to that of the time-series). The following equation was used to compute χ2 from the contingency table:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
