For every state-by-node TPM, there is one unique state-by-state TPM that is conditionally independent, which is outputted by PyPhi when converting a TPM from state-by-node to state-by-state form. We checked the extent to which our data met this property by taking the original state-by-state TPM, converting it to state-by-node, and then back to state-by-state. The relative distance D between the original TPM (A) and the conditionally independent TPM (B) was computed by subtracting the two arrays and calculating the Frobenius norm of the residual, which was divided by the Frobenius norm of the conditionally independent variant.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
